    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-duck-leg-with-plum-sauce-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then chop your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>into quarters (scrape the seeds and pith out with a spoon), then separate the <strong>white fat</strong> and the <strong>duck</strong> <strong>jelly</strong> from your <strong>duck leg[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!), top with the <strong>duck leg[s]</strong>, <strong>white fat</strong>, <strong>duck</strong> <strong>jelly</strong>, season with a<strong> </strong>pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>then<strong> </strong>put in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-duck-leg-with-plum-sauce-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s] </strong>lengthways until you have thin strips, then peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>spiced plum chutney </strong>and your<strong> hoisin sauce </strong>in a small bowl with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, your <strong>ginger paste </strong>and<strong> cornflour</strong></p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and mix well<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>plum mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-duck-leg-with-plum-sauce-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash, then add your <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander, pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt, then rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then combine with<strong> half</strong> your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-duck-leg-with-plum-sauce-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the duck has 10 min left, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>plum mix</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until reduced to a glossy sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>plum sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-duck-leg-with-plum-sauce-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cooled rice</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until everything is combined and the rice is heated through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-duck-leg-with-plum-sauce-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once combined, push the rice to one side of the pot and crack your <strong>egg[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into the other side</p><p>Stir the <strong>egg</strong> with a wooden spoon to break the yolk<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and cook for 1-2 min or until resembling scrambled egg</p><p>Once resembling scrambled egg, mix it all through the rice along with the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>egg fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-duck-leg-with-plum-sauce-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted duck leg</strong> and <strong>roasted pepper</strong> with the <strong>egg fried rice </strong>and <strong>sesame spinach</strong></p><p>Drizzle over any<strong> roasting juices</strong></p><p>Pour over the<strong> plum sauce</strong> and garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
